    // because G divides every element. If G is present, or if we can reach G, then every element becomes G.
    // However, the operation requires one element to divide another *currently* in the array.

    // The key insight from similar problems is that if we can reduce all numbers to the GCD of all numbers, 
    // that would be the minimum sum. Let's check if this is always possible.

    // Let $g = \text{GCD}(nums[0], nums[1], \ldots, nums[n-1])$.
