    // For $n_i$, we can try to replace it with the smallest $n_j$ such that $n_i \% n_j == 0$.
    // Since we want the *minimum* sum, we should use the smallest possible divisor available in the array.

    // If we use the smallest element $n_1$, any $n_i$ such that $n_i \% n_1 == 0$ can become $n_1$.
    // After this, $n_i$ is replaced by $n_1$. We repeat.

    // The set of achievable values for any element $x$ is the set of divisors of $x$ that are also present in the array (or can be created).
