    // If we have $G$ in the array, all elements become $G$.

    // What if $G$ is not in the array? E.g., [6, 10]. $\text{GCD}=2$. No operation possible. Sum=16.
    // The minimum sum is achieved when each $nums[i]$ becomes the smallest divisor $d$ of $nums[i]$ such that $d$ is in the set of elements that can divide $nums[i]$.

    // Let's use the property that if we can reduce $x \to y$ and $y \to z$, then $x \to z$.
    // The smallest value an element $x$ can reach is $d$, where $d$ is the smallest divisor of $x$ present in the set of numbers that can divide $x$ (transitively).

